verbose_text: We identified cases of ENT disease occurring in 2009, as recorded by the Korea National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey, and explored their associations with the levels of five air pollutants : sulfur dioxide (SO 2), nitrogen dioxide (NO 2), ozone (O 3), carbon monoxide (CO), and particulate matter (PM 10 particles; particulates < = 10 mum in aerodynamic diameter).
